# llama.cpp GGUF model manifest (rendered by chezmoi).
#
# Format (pipe-delimited, one model per line):
#   <hf-repo-id>|<hf-file>
#
# - hf-repo-id: Hugging Face repo id containing GGUF weights.
# - hf-file: GGUF file to place under ~/.llama.cpp/models/.
#
# Lines starting with `#` and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Downloads are opt-in via the `downloadLlamaCppModels` data variable in
# ~/.config/chezmoi/chezmoi.toml. Re-prompt by clearing that value.
#
# Strategy: keep the measured best local Qwen3.6 GGUF checkpoint, plus its
# refusal-removed (abliterated) sibling for prompts the stock model declines.

# Qwen3.6 35B-A3B Unsloth UD-Q4_K_XL (~22.4 GB GGUF).
# Unsloth dynamic (UD) quant: higher fidelity than stock Q4_K_M at the same
# size class, and the full 262144 context still co-fits in 36 GB unified memory
# with the q8_0 KV cache.
# https://huggingface.co/unsloth/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-GGUF
unsloth/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-GGUF|Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-UD-Q4_K_XL.gguf

# Qwen3.6 35B-A3B abliterated Q4_K_M (~21.2 GB GGUF).
# Refusal-removed sibling of the model above (abliteration of the same base,
# via wangzhang/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-abliterated). Same size class, loaded on demand.
# https://huggingface.co/mradermacher/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-abliterated-GGUF
mradermacher/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-abliterated-GGUF|Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-abliterated.Q4_K_M.gguf
